* Iron Raptor watches Prowl jump from her back and walk over to the pod, her 
pradictions right at the lack of movement.
It was a blank, a protoform without a spark.
She sighed, disappointed as well as Prowl. The Maximal forces could have 
used another player in this war, but it was just as well. One less soul 
which would be damned to fight a war on a losing side. One less spark to 
join the Matrix.

Iron Raptor them looked off across the plain, the large orange sun just 
touching the horizon.
She stepped towards the sun, the direction of the Ark.*

" We had better get moving then..."

* She then turned and looked over at Prowl, seeing the stump of his wing, 
wondering about just when he had ripped it off.
She sidled up beside him and nudged his shoulder with her snout, concern 
obviouse in her voice.*

" You alright?"

* She made a rough purring sound, cross betqeen a soft snarl and a low 
growl, her snout pressed to the back of Prowls shoulder, the only real 
action of affection since she had taken this twist in life.*
